WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:40.918 align:middle line:90%


00:00:40.918 --> 00:00:44.710 align:middle line:84%
Hey, Mikey, if I wasn't in such
great shape, could I do this?

00:00:44.710 --> 00:00:51.067 align:middle line:90%


00:00:51.067 --> 00:00:54.490 align:middle line:90%
That's stupid.

00:00:54.490 --> 00:00:56.460 align:middle line:90%
What if something goes wrong?

00:00:56.460 --> 00:00:57.350 align:middle line:90%
It's not.

00:00:57.350 --> 00:01:00.010 align:middle line:90%
Look, I'm not scared.

00:01:00.010 --> 00:01:01.660 align:middle line:90%
Hey, I got two kidneys.

00:01:01.660 --> 00:01:03.140 align:middle line:90%
You only need one.

00:01:03.140 --> 00:01:04.355 align:middle line:90%
No big deal, kiddo.

00:01:04.355 --> 00:01:07.882 align:middle line:90%


00:01:07.882 --> 00:01:08.581 align:middle line:90%
Stop it.

00:01:08.581 --> 00:01:42.754 align:middle line:90%


00:01:42.754 --> 00:01:45.234 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - KENT CURTNISS,
 "TIMING"]

00:01:45.234 --> 00:02:31.391 align:middle line:90%


00:02:31.391 --> 00:02:33.650 align:middle line:84%
-Really?
-Whoa, sugar, are you all right?

00:02:33.650 --> 00:02:34.454 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:02:34.454 --> 00:02:35.887 align:middle line:84%
What the heck is the
matter with that guy.

00:02:35.887 --> 00:02:37.477 align:middle line:84%
Let me straighten you
up here, sweetheart.

00:02:37.477 --> 00:02:38.371 align:middle line:90%
Jake.

00:02:38.371 --> 00:02:39.270 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

00:02:39.270 --> 00:02:40.170 align:middle line:90%
I'm just trying to help.

00:02:40.170 --> 00:02:42.500 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, you just keep
your hands to yourself.

00:02:42.500 --> 00:02:46.580 align:middle line:84%
You know, I try, but sometimes
they just get away from me.

00:02:46.580 --> 00:02:47.920 align:middle line:90%
I gotta go.

00:02:47.920 --> 00:02:48.880 align:middle line:90%
You knock 'em dead, huh?

00:02:48.880 --> 00:02:49.650 align:middle line:90%
Not that it'll matter.

00:02:49.650 --> 00:02:51.750 align:middle line:84%
And you've gotta believe
in yourself a little bit.

00:02:51.750 --> 00:02:52.770 align:middle line:90%
You're gonna do fine.

00:02:52.770 --> 00:02:54.520 align:middle line:84%
I know.
Thanks.

00:02:54.520 --> 00:02:56.620 align:middle line:90%
We believe in you.

00:02:56.620 --> 00:02:59.700 align:middle line:84%
I can smell the wind
of change a-coming.

00:02:59.700 --> 00:03:00.795 align:middle line:90%
Maybe that's just Wilbur.

00:03:00.795 --> 00:03:06.310 align:middle line:90%


00:03:06.310 --> 00:03:08.918 align:middle line:84%
Action is the key
to all success.

00:03:08.918 --> 00:03:10.910 align:middle line:90%
That Sophocles?

00:03:10.910 --> 00:03:12.404 align:middle line:90%
Picasso.

00:03:12.404 --> 00:03:14.894 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - KENT CURTNISS,
 "EVERYWHERE"]

00:03:14.894 --> 00:04:09.176 align:middle line:90%


00:04:09.176 --> 00:04:10.172 align:middle line:90%
Who writes this stuff?

00:04:10.172 --> 00:04:11.168 align:middle line:90%
Are you kidding me?

00:04:11.168 --> 00:04:12.865 align:middle line:90%
[INAUDIBLE] in our schools?

00:04:12.865 --> 00:04:15.660 align:middle line:84%
And the actors through these
wild parties which included--

00:04:15.660 --> 00:04:18.067 align:middle line:90%
now get this-- wifeswapping!

00:04:18.067 --> 00:04:19.560 align:middle line:90%
What the is that?

00:04:19.560 --> 00:04:20.630 align:middle line:90%
You're buying their movies!

00:04:20.630 --> 00:04:22.290 align:middle line:90%
Think about it!

00:04:22.290 --> 00:04:23.988 align:middle line:84%
You know what I
think we oughta do?

00:04:23.988 --> 00:04:25.601 align:middle line:84%
Cock the gun, blow
their brains out!

00:04:25.601 --> 00:04:27.035 align:middle line:84%
Booyah!
No more--

00:04:27.035 --> 00:04:36.735 align:middle line:90%


00:04:36.735 --> 00:04:37.891 align:middle line:84%
-Miss Louis?
-Yes.

00:04:37.891 --> 00:04:40.113 align:middle line:84%
Katie Dawkins.
I'm here for the interview.

00:04:40.113 --> 00:04:40.980 align:middle line:90%
Oh, right.

00:04:40.980 --> 00:04:41.680 align:middle line:90%
Have a seat.

00:04:41.680 --> 00:04:45.700 align:middle line:90%


00:04:45.700 --> 00:04:46.790 align:middle line:90%
You've got 10 minutes.

00:04:46.790 --> 00:04:47.805 align:middle line:90%
Sell me.

00:04:47.805 --> 00:04:49.140 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:04:49.140 --> 00:04:52.540 align:middle line:84%
Your latest viewer
poll shows that 67%

00:04:52.540 --> 00:04:53.790 align:middle line:84%
of Boulder Tonight's
viewers want

00:04:53.790 --> 00:04:56.660 align:middle line:90%
more positive news stories.

00:04:56.660 --> 00:04:59.810 align:middle line:84%
Yet, your-- your show
continues to fill

00:04:59.810 --> 00:05:03.317 align:middle line:84%
the air with political unrest,
celebrity scandal, crime--

00:05:03.317 --> 00:05:05.050 align:middle line:84%
You think you're going to
get a job here by telling

00:05:05.050 --> 00:05:06.650 align:middle line:84%
me what I'm doing wrong?
-No.

00:05:06.650 --> 00:05:08.400 align:middle line:84%
Which satellite do you
want for the Bloomboy story?

00:05:08.400 --> 00:05:09.150 align:middle line:90%
Chris already knows.

00:05:09.150 --> 00:05:10.720 align:middle line:90%
Ask him about it.

00:05:10.720 --> 00:05:15.456 align:middle line:84%
No, there just might be
space for more a upbeat story.

00:05:15.456 --> 00:05:18.322 align:middle line:90%
Look, I've done my research.

00:05:18.322 --> 00:05:21.030 align:middle line:84%
Just let me show
you one interview.

00:05:21.030 --> 00:05:23.470 align:middle line:90%
I know I have a story here.

00:05:23.470 --> 00:05:25.832 align:middle line:84%
I have nine minutes
left, don't I?

00:05:25.832 --> 00:05:28.360 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
OK.

00:05:28.360 --> 00:05:35.580 align:middle line:90%


00:05:35.580 --> 00:05:40.840 align:middle line:84%
Our research has shown that the
same deep brain structures that

00:05:40.840 --> 00:05:46.200 align:middle line:84%
are activated when we receive
a reward, like money or food,

00:05:46.200 --> 00:05:48.980 align:middle line:84%
those very same brain
areas are activated

00:05:48.980 --> 00:05:54.420 align:middle line:84%
even more when we give to an
organization that we support.

00:05:54.420 --> 00:05:55.560 align:middle line:90%
That's a great study.

00:05:55.560 --> 00:05:57.750 align:middle line:84%
Paid for with our tax
studies, I assume.

00:05:57.750 --> 00:06:01.760 align:middle line:84%
He's the chief scientist at the
National Institute of Health.

00:06:01.760 --> 00:06:02.760 align:middle line:90%
They just published his study.

00:06:02.760 --> 00:06:04.030 align:middle line:84%
Wow, that's--
that's really great.

00:06:04.030 --> 00:06:04.860 align:middle line:90%
Terry--

00:06:04.860 --> 00:06:07.770 align:middle line:84%
Katie Dawkins, Mike Wilson,
our lead segment producer.

00:06:07.770 --> 00:06:08.990 align:middle line:90%
Terry, I need to talk to you.

00:06:08.990 --> 00:06:11.050 align:middle line:90%
Wait your turn.

00:06:11.050 --> 00:06:12.630 align:middle line:90%
So what's your angle?

00:06:12.630 --> 00:06:13.680 align:middle line:90%
KATIE: Sorry?

00:06:13.680 --> 00:06:14.600 align:middle line:90%
Your angle?

00:06:14.600 --> 00:06:16.620 align:middle line:90%
Your lead?

00:06:16.620 --> 00:06:20.350 align:middle line:84%
For the first time, we have
scientific proof from the NIH

00:06:20.350 --> 00:06:23.267 align:middle line:84%
that living a compassionate
life and treating people

00:06:23.267 --> 00:06:24.899 align:middle line:84%
with kindness can actually--
MIKE: Oh my god.

00:06:24.899 --> 00:06:26.710 align:middle line:90%
Are you kidding me?

00:06:26.710 --> 00:06:28.420 align:middle line:90%
Make you happy.

00:06:28.420 --> 00:06:31.653 align:middle line:84%
TERRY: Who else do you have?
-Oh come on.

00:06:31.653 --> 00:06:33.780 align:middle line:84%
Tell me you've get some
politicians, celebrities,

00:06:33.780 --> 00:06:36.230 align:middle line:90%
hot models, anything?

00:06:36.230 --> 00:06:38.185 align:middle line:84%
You can't come in here with
one scientist and tell us

00:06:38.185 --> 00:06:39.785 align:middle line:84%
you've nailed down a story.
TERRY: Mike, that's enough.

00:06:39.785 --> 00:06:41.760 align:middle line:90%
How about Deepak Chopra?

00:06:41.760 --> 00:06:43.119 align:middle line:90%
TERRY: You have Deepak?

00:06:43.119 --> 00:06:44.485 align:middle line:84%
Not yet, but I spoke
with his assistant,

00:06:44.485 --> 00:06:46.771 align:middle line:84%
and he's going to be
in town this week.

00:06:46.771 --> 00:06:47.770 align:middle line:90%
Oh, you spoke with assistant.

00:06:47.770 --> 00:06:48.470 align:middle line:90%
That's great.

00:06:48.470 --> 00:06:50.720 align:middle line:84%
Why don't you go interview
my-- my cousin Al too?

00:06:50.720 --> 00:06:52.170 align:middle line:84%
OK?
Don't waste our time.

00:06:52.170 --> 00:06:52.900 align:middle line:90%
Look, Terry.

00:06:52.900 --> 00:06:54.720 align:middle line:84%
TERRY: Miss Dawkins,
I'll give you a shot.

00:06:54.720 --> 00:06:56.440 align:middle line:84%
Strictly freelance until
you prove yourself.

00:06:56.440 --> 00:06:57.880 align:middle line:84%
No, no, no.
That-- that's fluff.

00:06:57.880 --> 00:06:58.860 align:middle line:90%
We don't do fluff, OK?

00:06:58.860 --> 00:06:59.950 align:middle line:90%
Your rules, not mine.

00:06:59.950 --> 00:07:02.087 align:middle line:90%
Well, maybe we should start.

00:07:02.087 --> 00:07:03.752 align:middle line:84%
MIKE: I mean, she's a rookie.
Look at her.

00:07:03.752 --> 00:07:04.825 align:middle line:90%
I know.

00:07:04.825 --> 00:07:07.040 align:middle line:90%
That's where you come in.

00:07:07.040 --> 00:07:09.221 align:middle line:84%
Oh, no, no, no, There's
no way that you--

00:07:09.221 --> 00:07:09.920 align:middle line:90%
Stop.

00:07:09.920 --> 00:07:12.446 align:middle line:84%
You know that weekend
anchor position?

00:07:12.446 --> 00:07:15.170 align:middle line:90%
Ah, you wouldn't dare.

00:07:15.170 --> 00:07:16.290 align:middle line:90%
What about the Senator?

00:07:16.290 --> 00:07:18.900 align:middle line:84%
Mike, I need an experienced
reporter on this.

00:07:18.900 --> 00:07:22.090 align:middle line:84%
Full story, ready for a
rundown, 5 o'clock Saturday,

00:07:22.090 --> 00:07:23.940 align:middle line:90%
not a minute late.

00:07:23.940 --> 00:07:25.830 align:middle line:84%
And it better
knock my socks off.

00:07:25.830 --> 00:07:29.988 align:middle line:90%


00:07:29.988 --> 00:07:34.570 align:middle line:10%
What we discovered was that
the reward systems of the brain,

00:07:34.570 --> 00:07:38.330 align:middle line:10%
which are located very deep
in primitive brain areas,

00:07:38.330 --> 00:07:40.730 align:middle line:10%
were activated when
people received

00:07:40.730 --> 00:07:43.420 align:middle line:10%
money, which is expected.

00:07:43.420 --> 00:07:45.560 align:middle line:84%
Other researchers have
shown that same thing

00:07:45.560 --> 00:07:47.640 align:middle line:90%
for many decades now.

00:07:47.640 --> 00:07:52.400 align:middle line:84%
However, what surprised
us was when people donated

00:07:52.400 --> 00:07:55.330 align:middle line:84%
to nonprofit organizations,
were willing to give money,

00:07:55.330 --> 00:07:59.020 align:middle line:84%
to take it from their own
savings that we gave them

00:07:59.020 --> 00:08:01.180 align:middle line:84%
and donate it to
an organization,

00:08:01.180 --> 00:08:04.710 align:middle line:84%
the same reward systems in
the brain became activated.

00:08:04.710 --> 00:08:07.730 align:middle line:84%
And not only were they
activated in a similar way,

00:08:07.730 --> 00:08:10.100 align:middle line:84%
they were actually more
activated than when

00:08:10.100 --> 00:08:11.890 align:middle line:90%
people simply received money.

00:08:11.890 --> 00:08:13.740 align:middle line:84%
So that was a big
surprise to us.

00:08:13.740 --> 00:08:16.080 align:middle line:10%
There is a feeling of
euphoria that many people

00:08:16.080 --> 00:08:21.210 align:middle line:10%
describe giving back to people,
doing charity work, and so on.

00:08:21.210 --> 00:08:33.510 align:middle line:90%


00:08:33.510 --> 00:08:34.500 align:middle line:90%
Good morning.

00:08:34.500 --> 00:08:36.900 align:middle line:84%
Ah, you're always
bringing us fresh coffee.

00:08:36.900 --> 00:08:38.370 align:middle line:90%
And you're always taking it.

00:08:38.370 --> 00:08:40.429 align:middle line:90%
Well, I wouldn't wanna be rude.

00:08:40.429 --> 00:08:42.150 align:middle line:84%
So where's the job
interview today?

00:08:42.150 --> 00:08:43.230 align:middle line:90%
No interview.

00:08:43.230 --> 00:08:44.760 align:middle line:90%
I got the job, Boulder Tonight.

00:08:44.760 --> 00:08:46.470 align:middle line:90%
You mean those guys over at--

00:08:46.470 --> 00:08:48.680 align:middle line:90%
Hey, it's a job, isn't it?

00:08:48.680 --> 00:08:50.390 align:middle line:84%
Besides, if I
didn't get one soon,

00:08:50.390 --> 00:08:53.530 align:middle line:84%
I know someone who'd be out
of their morning coffees.

00:08:53.530 --> 00:08:59.430 align:middle line:84%
I like my coffee like I like
my women-- in a plastic cup.

00:08:59.430 --> 00:09:00.790 align:middle line:90%
Where does he get these?

00:09:00.790 --> 00:09:01.490 align:middle line:90%
I dunno.

00:09:01.490 --> 00:09:02.995 align:middle line:90%
One day, it's Albert Einstein.

00:09:02.995 --> 00:09:04.380 align:middle line:90%
The next day, it's Eddie Izzard.

00:09:04.380 --> 00:09:05.779 align:middle line:84%
All right, guys.
I gotta go.

00:09:05.779 --> 00:09:07.113 align:middle line:84%
Well, you know
'em dead, sweetie.

00:09:07.113 --> 00:09:07.812 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:09:07.812 --> 00:09:10.488 align:middle line:90%


00:09:10.488 --> 00:09:13.710 align:middle line:90%
You know, she ain't bad.

00:09:13.710 --> 00:09:14.790 align:middle line:90%
No, not her.

00:09:14.790 --> 00:09:16.040 align:middle line:90%
The new girl over there.

00:09:16.040 --> 00:09:19.610 align:middle line:84%
Oh, it's been a long time
since I rock n' rolled.

00:09:19.610 --> 00:09:22.180 align:middle line:90%
Albert Einstein?

00:09:22.180 --> 00:09:23.710 align:middle line:90%
Led Zeppelin.

00:09:23.710 --> 00:09:25.100 align:middle line:84%
You know, I never
know with you.

00:09:25.100 --> 00:09:28.058 align:middle line:90%


00:09:28.058 --> 00:09:31.016 align:middle line:84%
(SINGING): You're
wondering if I'll miss you.

00:09:31.016 --> 00:09:36.932 align:middle line:90%


00:09:36.932 --> 00:09:42.848 align:middle line:84%
Oh, in my heart, you'll always
be there every step of the way.

00:09:42.848 --> 00:09:47.778 align:middle line:90%


00:09:47.778 --> 00:09:50.795 align:middle line:90%
I'm so gonna miss you.

00:09:50.795 --> 00:09:55.565 align:middle line:84%
You're my best friend
in the whole world.

00:09:55.565 --> 00:10:00.760 align:middle line:84%
Believe me when I tell
you, you're so incredible.

00:10:00.760 --> 00:10:05.035 align:middle line:84%
Don't you know
you're unforgettable?

00:10:05.035 --> 00:10:06.950 align:middle line:90%
[TYPING]

00:10:06.950 --> 00:10:11.050 align:middle line:84%
We've known for over
20 years that people

00:10:11.050 --> 00:10:15.520 align:middle line:84%
who are compassionate and
empathic with other people

00:10:15.520 --> 00:10:18.470 align:middle line:90%
have a sense of fulfillment.

00:10:18.470 --> 00:10:23.040 align:middle line:84%
They have what has been
called the helper's high.

00:10:23.040 --> 00:10:26.020 align:middle line:90%
Mind if I drive?

00:10:26.020 --> 00:10:28.065 align:middle line:90%
I guess not.

00:10:28.065 --> 00:10:30.070 align:middle line:84%
I need tighter, shorter
cuts if you're ever

00:10:30.070 --> 00:10:32.890 align:middle line:90%
gonna get this on here, OK?

00:10:32.890 --> 00:10:35.698 align:middle line:84%
I assume you have
some B roll for this?

00:10:35.698 --> 00:10:37.180 align:middle line:90%
Put it right in there.

00:10:37.180 --> 00:10:43.260 align:middle line:84%
People who do volunteer work,
compassionate, empathic work

00:10:43.260 --> 00:10:46.020 align:middle line:84%
in which they deeply
care for someone else,

00:10:46.020 --> 00:10:47.950 align:middle line:84%
have not only a
sense of well being,

00:10:47.950 --> 00:10:52.470 align:middle line:84%
often a sense of euphoria,
they also have increase

00:10:52.470 --> 00:10:53.650 align:middle line:90%
in their health profiles.

00:10:53.650 --> 00:10:55.850 align:middle line:90%
They get sick less.

00:10:55.850 --> 00:10:57.300 align:middle line:90%
That's better.

00:10:57.300 --> 00:10:58.260 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:10:58.260 --> 00:11:00.660 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, whatever.

00:11:00.660 --> 00:11:02.634 align:middle line:84%
So who else do you
have in the can?

00:11:02.634 --> 00:11:04.340 align:middle line:84%
Well, we have Dr.
Dossey, and Dr. Grafman.

00:11:04.340 --> 00:11:06.940 align:middle line:90%


00:11:06.940 --> 00:11:07.810 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:11:07.810 --> 00:11:09.043 align:middle line:84%
So I guess the rest
of the interviews

00:11:09.043 --> 00:11:11.410 align:middle line:90%
are just gonna magically appear.

00:11:11.410 --> 00:11:12.330 align:middle line:90%
Nice.

00:11:12.330 --> 00:11:13.750 align:middle line:90%
I believe in this story.

00:11:13.750 --> 00:11:16.100 align:middle line:84%
Oh, that's nice, Katie.
All right.

00:11:16.100 --> 00:11:17.960 align:middle line:90%
We don't have time for this, OK?

00:11:17.960 --> 00:11:19.040 align:middle line:90%
We-- we need names.

00:11:19.040 --> 00:11:19.920 align:middle line:90%
We need big names.

00:11:19.920 --> 00:11:22.700 align:middle line:84%
And we have, like, five days to
get this going, I don't know--

00:11:22.700 --> 00:11:24.270 align:middle line:90%
[BUZZING]

00:11:24.270 --> 00:11:25.410 align:middle line:90%
Katie Dawkins?

00:11:25.410 --> 00:11:26.780 align:middle line:90%
That's rude.

00:11:26.780 --> 00:11:28.930 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:11:28.930 --> 00:11:32.440 align:middle line:84%
No, thank you for
calling me back.

00:11:32.440 --> 00:11:33.830 align:middle line:90%
That would be great.

00:11:33.830 --> 00:11:35.310 align:middle line:90%
No, of course.

00:11:35.310 --> 00:11:36.700 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:11:36.700 --> 00:11:38.170 align:middle line:90%
Yes, thank you so much.

00:11:38.170 --> 00:11:40.930 align:middle line:90%


00:11:40.930 --> 00:11:43.640 align:middle line:90%
Can we use the studio?

00:11:43.640 --> 00:11:45.350 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:11:45.350 --> 00:11:47.030 align:middle line:90%
That was Deepak Chopra.

00:11:47.030 --> 00:11:48.020 align:middle line:90%
On your phone?

00:11:48.020 --> 00:11:50.610 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, he had time before
his lecture tonight at CU.

00:11:50.610 --> 00:11:51.360 align:middle line:90%
He's on his way over.

00:11:51.360 --> 00:11:52.060 align:middle line:90%
Wait, wait, wait.

00:11:52.060 --> 00:11:53.970 align:middle line:84%
How did you get Deepak
to call you on your--

00:11:53.970 --> 00:11:55.187 align:middle line:90%
I told you.

00:11:55.187 --> 00:11:55.920 align:middle line:90%
