00:23:11.590 --> 00:23:12.580 align:middle line:10%
for example.

00:23:12.580 --> 00:23:14.030 align:middle line:84%
So they took a number
of participants

00:23:14.030 --> 00:23:15.210 align:middle line:90%
through this study.

00:23:15.210 --> 00:23:17.170 align:middle line:84%
And they were young
and old, from very

00:23:17.170 --> 00:23:18.740 align:middle line:90%
different backgrounds.

00:23:18.740 --> 00:23:22.290 align:middle line:84%
And they-- so the participants
watched a two minute clip.

00:23:22.290 --> 00:23:24.465 align:middle line:84%
And in this two minute clip--
it could be of Mother Theresa.

00:23:24.465 --> 00:23:26.250 align:middle line:84%
It could be just
someone building--

00:23:26.250 --> 00:23:27.530 align:middle line:84%
helping someone
build a playhouse

00:23:27.530 --> 00:23:28.740 align:middle line:90%
for someone, and so on.

00:23:28.740 --> 00:23:31.630 align:middle line:84%
And two remarkable
results came to the fore.

00:23:31.630 --> 00:23:33.540 align:middle line:84%
The first was that
people immediately

00:23:33.540 --> 00:23:35.870 align:middle line:84%
